# Methods

## Data

### Acquiring Species Occurrence Data

Explain your occurence data. Source, how many and the years etc.. 

```{r include=FALSE}
library(biomod2)
library(raster)
library(dismo)
library(sp)
library(dplyr)

#change the related part for you selected species
#change all "aedes" variables below

aedes <- gbif('your selection genus', 'your selection species', ext=NULL, args=NULL, geo=TRUE, sp=TRUE, 
              removeZeros=TRUE, download=TRUE, ntries=5, start = 1, end = 300) 


aedes.df <- data.frame(aedes)
aedesXY <- aedes.df[,c('lon','lat')]
aedesdfs <- slice_sample(aedesXY, n = 100, replace = FALSE) 

```

### Formating Data for biomod2

Eplain which layers do you use

```{r include=FALSE}
myRespName <- 'aedes.albopictus'
myResp <- SpatialPoints(coords = aedesdfs, proj4string = CRS(as.character(NA)), bbox = NULL)
myRespXY <- data.frame(aedesdfs)

#Why did you choose these parameters, write clearly

bio1 <- raster("wc2.1_5m_bio_1.tif") #Annual Mean Temperature
bio2 <- raster("wc2.1_5m_bio_2.tif") #Mean Diurnal Range
bio12 <- raster("wc2.1_5m_bio_12.tif") #Annual Precipitation

myExpl <- stack(bio1, bio2, bio12)
plot(myExpl)

myBiomodData <- BIOMOD_FormatingData(resp.var=myResp,
                                     expl.var = myExpl,
                                     resp.xy= myRespXY,
                                     resp.name=myRespName,
                                     PA.nb.rep = 1,
                                     PA.nb.absences = 100,
                                     PA.strategy = 'random',
                                     na.rm = TRUE)

```

### Acquiring Historical & Future Bioclimatic Variables

[Historical bioclimatic variables](https://www.worldclim.org/data/worldclim21.html) were acquired from WorldClim website with 5 minutes spatial resolution ^[6]^.

[Future bioclimatic variables](https://www.worldclim.org/data/cmip6/cmip6_clim5m.html) were acquired from WorldClim website with 5 minutes spatial resolution for 2021-2040 time period and MIROC6 estimations for SSP370 ^[7]^. 

WHY do you use these explain in the text?

## Modeling

EXPLAIN you modelling apporach. Which algorithms do you use? How many replicates do you makes.
Can you merge them (ensemble?)?


```{r include=FALSE}
myBiomodModelout <- BIOMOD_Modeling(bm.format = myBiomodData,
                                    modeling.id = paste(myRespName,"Modeling",sep=""),
                                    models = c('GAM', 'MAXENT.Phillips'),
                                    nb.rep = 1,
                                    data.split.perc = 80,
                                    prevalence = 0.5,
                                    var.import = 3,
                                    metric.eval = c('ROC', 'TSS'),
                                    scale.models = TRUE,
                                    do.full.models = FALSE)
```

## Projections

Both projections were done by **BIOMOD_Projection** function of **biomod2** R package. 
 
### Current Projection

Explain which period do you project?
Future or present.

```{r include=FALSE}
myBiomodProj <- BIOMOD_Projection(bm.mod = myBiomodModelout,
                                  new.env = myExpl,
                                  proj.name = 'current',
                                  models.chosen = 'all',
                                  metric.binary = c('ROC', 'TSS'),
                                  compress = TRUE,
                                  clamping.mask=F)
```

### Future or Past???? Projection

Which period, which climate model do you select and which ssp? 

```{r include=FALSE}
abio <- raster::stack("future.tif")
a_bio1 <- subset(abio, 'future_1')
a_bio2 <- subset(abio, 'future_2')
a_bio12 <- subset(abio, 'future_12')

myExplFuture <- stack(a_bio1, a_bio2, a_bio12)
names(myExplFuture) = names(myExpl)
plot(myExplFuture)
```

```{r include=FALSE}
myBiomodProjFut <- BIOMOD_Projection(bm.mod = myBiomodModelout,
                                     new.env = myExplFuture,
                                     proj.name = 'future',
                                     models.chosen = 'all',
                                     metric.binary = c('ROC', 'TSS'),
                                     compress = TRUE,
                                     clamping.mask= F)
```

